'''mySimon''' is a [[Price comparison service|comparison shopping website]] owned by [[CBS Interactive]]. The site offers shopping recommendations, buying advice, and side by side price comparisons for various products. Founded in 1998, mySimon was acquired in 2000 for $700 million.<ref>{{cite news | first = Clint | last = Boulton | title = CNET Acquires mySimon | date = 2000-01-20 | url = http://www.internetnews.com/ec-news/article.php/289951/CNET+Acquires+mySimon.htm | work = InternetNews.com | accessdate = 2013-10-15}}</ref> mySimon was also nominated for a Webby award in 2001.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://winners.webbyawards.com/2001/web/general-website/commerce | title = Commerce / The Webby Awards / 2001 | accessdate = 2013-10-15}}</ref> The site directs users to other shopping sites such as [[Amazon (company)|Amazon.com]] when searching for products. It is not affiliated with [[Simon Property Group]], a mall operator.

